This paper focuses on the use of automatically generated patches by developers when fixing software defects, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The study involves modifying code, which is also relevant to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of automated tools to generate patches involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The study also involves testing and validating patches, which is relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the study involves analyzing and characterizing developer behavior, which is relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
